03/03/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia's Security Council has decided to support a proposal by Interior Minister Hari Kostov, establishing a joint governmental-parliamentary commission. 
Its mission would be to determine the fate of 18 Macedonian and ethnic Albanian citizens, missing since the 2001 military conflict. 
The Council met on Friday (28 February), and included members of the new cabinet. 
In addition, there are representatives from the previous governments as well as former members of the National Liberation Army and incumbent lawmakers from the Democratic Union for Integration. 
The Council also discussed the activities of rebel groups, the future law on collecting illegal weapons and the country's position on a possible war in Iraq. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Vest, Dnevnik- 03/03/03; A1 TV - 01/03/03)
